##
# cc_deny
#
# Country Code deny list — block traffic from/to countries listed here.
# Requires ipset (USE_IPSET="auto" or "1") for high-performance matching.
#
# Format: one entry per line, blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# Simple syntax — block all traffic from/to a country:
#   CN
#   RU
#
# Continent shorthand — expands to all countries in the continent:
#   @EU
#   @AS
#
# Supported continents: @AF (Africa), @AS (Asia), @EU (Europe),
# @NA (North America), @SA (South America), @OC (Oceania)
#
# Advanced syntax — block specific protocol/port/direction per country:
#   proto:flow:[s/d]=port:[s/d]=CC
#
# Examples:
#   Block inbound SSH from China:       tcp:in:d=22:s=CN
#   Block inbound SMTP from Russia:     tcp:in:d=25:s=RU
#   Block inbound to ports 80,443:      tcp:in:d=80:s=BR
#
# Wildcard (*) in advanced entries expands to all simple CCs in this file:
#   Block inbound SSH from all denied countries: tcp:in:d=22:s=*
#
# Temporary entries use the same ttl=/expire= syntax as allow/deny_hosts.rules.
#
##
